<br>
Make a hotkey:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> /language #<br>
/g hate<br>
/language #<br>
/g fear</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
This will teach two languages at the same time.<br>
<br>
To get creative you could setup two hotkeys and teach 5 languages:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> /language #<br>
/g hate<br>
/language #<br>
/g fear<br>
/language #<br>
<br>
/g envy<br>
/language #<br>
/g pain<br>
/language #<br>
/g barsh</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Just click first hotkey, let it cycle, then click second. Repeat. <p><p align="left"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="+2" color="#FF0000"><b><font size="+1">Obeah<br><a href="http://www.geocities.com/midnightcouncil"><img src="http://fantazone.com/mcresources/mcsig.jpg" border=0></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/uheladeville.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hela D Eville</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Council Member</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#939393>(1/30/01 7:59:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Teaching Languages</span><hr size=1> I'll try that.  I find that the med period between barshings (as well as the obnoxious forever boat trips) are excellent places to teach languages.  The technique I was taught is to open a social, hotkey it as Lang. and fill the entire text block with single sentence group statements:<br>
